---
const skills = [
  'User-Centred Design',
  'Strategy',
  'Design Operations',
  'AI-Augmented Workflows',
  'Team Leadership',
  'UI Craft',
  'Workshop Facilitation',
  'Design Systems',
];
---

<section id="about" class="about container section" aria-labelledby="about-h">
  <div class="about-grid">
    <aside class="about-quote">
      <span class="mono about-eyebrow">About</span>
      <p class="quote serif-display">
        <span class="quote-mark" aria-hidden="true">“</span>
        I lead like
        <span class="italic accent">Phil Jackson</span>
        — set the system, build the trust, then get out of the way.
      </p>
      <p class="quote-attr mono">— Personal operating principle</p>
    </aside>

    <div class="about-bio">
      <h2 id="about-h" class="bio-title serif-display">
        Fifteen years of design leadership.
      </h2>
      <p>
        I'm a Product Design Lead currently rebuilding the design organisation
        at <strong>Randstad Digital Marketplace</strong> around AI-augmented workflows.
        Before this I led design for a fintech venture builder
        (<strong>ICEO</strong>, scaling a 3-person team to 9), shaped consumer
        experience at <strong>Just Eat Takeaway</strong> across 22 markets, and
        worked across <strong>Wallapop</strong> and <strong>ING</strong> before that.
      </p>
      <p>
        My pattern: walk into design teams that are stuck in execution, and rebuild
        them around strategy, rituals, and cross-functional trust. I'm a
        <strong>DISC profile <em>D/I</em></strong> — direct, fast, restless about
        progress. Pragmatic over precious. I care more about the system that
        produces the work than any single artefact.
      </p>
      <ul class="skill-pills mono" role="list">
        {skills.map(s => <li>{s}</li>)}
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.2fr;
    gap: 80px;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .about-eyebrow {
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    display: inline-block;
  }

  .quote {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: clamp(28px, 3.2vw, 44px);
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--fg);
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    text-wrap: balance;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .quote-mark {
    font-size: 1.6em;
    color: var(--c-orange);
    line-height: 0;
    vertical-align: -0.2em;
    margin-right: 4px;
  }
  .quote .accent { color: var(--c-orange); font-weight: 400; }
  .quote-attr { color: var(--muted); }

  .about-bio { display: grid; gap: 20px; }
  .bio-title {
    font-size: var(--t-h2);
    font-weight: 300;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    max-width: 18ch;
    color: var(--fg);
  }
  .about-bio p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(16px, 1.4vw, 18px);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--fg);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }
  .about-bio strong {
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--c-orange);
  }
  .about-bio strong em { font-style: normal; }

  .skill-pills {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 16px 0 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 8px;
  }
  .skill-pills li {
    padding: 6px 12px;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: var(--bg-2);
    color: var(--muted);
    font-size: 10px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .about-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 40px; }
  }
</style>
